(
<figureCitation id="132F2A6BC965FFD27E9BFD0C1EAC129C" box="[159,229,724,750]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[204,1377,207,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-72@27.[195,1382,194,1878]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 8. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Apomatus ampulliferus. France, Marseille, 200 m, legit F.J.A. Pantus, ZMA V.Pol. 3812. A—uncini of 4th thoracic chaetiger, B—anterior abdominal uncini, details of peg, C—details of Apomatus chaetae in 7th thoracic chaetiger, D—details of Apomatus chaetae in 4th thoracic chaetiger, E—middle abdominal chaetae, F—details of E." pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAB36EEC965FFD27E93FCF91C80134A" blockId="26.[151,713,801,856]" box="[151,713,801,825]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27E93FCF91F6F134B" bold="true" box="[151,294,801,825]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Type-species</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC965FFD27F30FCF91C80134A" authority="Philippi, 1844" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1844" box="[308,713,801,824]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Apomatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ampulliferus">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27F30FCF91C65134A" box="[308,556,801,824]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Apomatus ampulliferus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF854B1FC965FFD27C36FCF91C80134A" author="Philippi, A." box="[562,713,801,824]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="153 - 162" refId="ref65759" refString="Philippi, A. (1844) Einige Bemerkungen uber die Gattung Serpula, nebst Aufzahlung der von mir im Mittelmeer mit dem Thier beobachteten Arten. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, Berlin, 10, 186 - 198. (translated in: Annals and Magazine of Natural History London (1), 14, 153 - 162)." type="journal article" year="1844">Philippi, 1844</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAB36EEC965FFD27E93FC991F33132A" blockId="26.[151,713,801,856]" box="[151,378,833,856]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Number of species: 7</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAB36EEC965FFD27E93FC501EBA15EA" blockId="26.[151,1436,904,1819]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Tube white, opaque, circular in cross-section, keels and collar-like rings absent. Granular overlay may be present. Operculum a soft membranous vesicle without endplate borne on unmodified pinnulated radiole. Opercular constriction may be present. Pseudoperculum may be present on unmodified radiole. Arrangement of radioles in semi-circles (may be up to ¾ of a circle), maximum number up to 40 per lobe in larger species. Inter-radiolar membrane present. Branchial eyes present in the form of ocellar clusters. Stylodes absent. Mouth palps present. 7 thoracic chaetigerous segments. Collar trilobed with smooth edge. Thoracic membrane long, forming ventral apron across anterior abdominal segments. Tonguelets between ventral and lateral collar lobes absent. Collar chaetae limbate, of two sizes (thus, in the classical terminology capillary and limbate). 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC965FFD27E93FB651F4514A4" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1844" box="[151,268,1213,1238]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Apomatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27E93FB651F4514A4" box="[151,268,1213,1238]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Apomatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
chaetae present (
<figureCitation id="132F2A6BC965FFD27FDAFB651C2A14A5" box="[478,611,1213,1239]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[204,1377,207,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-72@27.[195,1382,194,1878]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 8. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Apomatus ampulliferus. France, Marseille, 200 m, legit F.J.A. Pantus, ZMA V.Pol. 3812. A—uncini of 4th thoracic chaetiger, B—anterior abdominal uncini, details of peg, C—details of Apomatus chaetae in 7th thoracic chaetiger, D—details of Apomatus chaetae in 4th thoracic chaetiger, E—middle abdominal chaetae, F—details of E." pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 8C, D</figureCitation>
). Thoracic uncini saw-to-rasp-shaped with approximately 30 teeth in profile, up to 3 (exceptionally 4) teeth in a row above and continuing onto peg; anterior peg very long, blunt, almost rectangular (
<figureCitation id="132F2A6BC965FFD27F8DFAD21C581556" box="[393,529,1290,1316]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[204,1377,207,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-72@27.[195,1382,194,1878]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 8. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Apomatus ampulliferus. France, Marseille, 200 m, legit F.J.A. Pantus, ZMA V.Pol. 3812. A—uncini of 4th thoracic chaetiger, B—anterior abdominal uncini, details of peg, C—details of Apomatus chaetae in 7th thoracic chaetiger, D—details of Apomatus chaetae in 4th thoracic chaetiger, E—middle abdominal chaetae, F—details of E." pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 8A, B</figureCitation>
). Ventral thoracic triangular depression absent. Abdominal chaetae sickleshaped with finely denticulate blades (
<figureCitation id="132F2A6BC965FFD27C5BFAE91C9D1539" box="[607,724,1329,1355]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[204,1377,207,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-72@27.[195,1382,194,1878]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 8. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Apomatus ampulliferus. France, Marseille, 200 m, legit F.J.A. Pantus, ZMA V.Pol. 3812. A—uncini of 4th thoracic chaetiger, B—anterior abdominal uncini, details of peg, C—details of Apomatus chaetae in 7th thoracic chaetiger, D—details of Apomatus chaetae in 4th thoracic chaetiger, E—middle abdominal chaetae, F—details of E." pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig 8E, F</figureCitation>
); uncini rasp-shaped with approximately 30 teeth in profile. Short achaetous anterior abdominal zone present. Posterior capillary chaetae present. Posterior glandular pad present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30E6565C965FFD47EC2FA7D1B0F108C" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAB36EEC965FFD27EC2FA7D1F321769" blockId="26.[151,1436,904,1819]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27EC2FA7D1F7615CD" bold="true" box="[198,319,1445,1471]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Remarks.</emphasis>
A controversy exists whether 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC965FFD27CA6FA7D1CB315CC" authorityName="Risso" authorityYear="1826" box="[674,762,1445,1470]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Protula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27CA6FA7D1CB315CC" box="[674,762,1445,1470]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Protula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC965FFD27D37FA7D1DE115CC" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1844" box="[819,936,1445,1470]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Apomatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27D37FA7D1DE115CC" box="[819,936,1445,1470]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Apomatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be regarded as separate genera (ten 
<bibRefCitation id="EF854B1FC965FFD27E93FA141FC71594" author="Hove, H. A. ten &amp; Pantus, F. J. A." box="[151,398,1484,1510]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="419 - 437" refId="ref61262" refString="Hove, H. A. ten &amp; Pantus, F. J. A. (1985) Distinguishing the genera Apomatus Philippi, 1844 and Protula Risso, 1826 (Polychaeta: Serpulidae). A further plea for a methodical approach to serpulid taxonomy. Zoologische Mededelingen (Leiden), 59, 419 - 437." type="journal article" year="1985">Hove &amp; Pantus 1985</bibRefCitation>
) or synonymized under 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC965FFD27CAFFA141A251594" authority="(Kupriyanova &amp; Jirkov 1997)" baseAuthorityName="Kupriyanova &amp; Jirkov" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[683,1132,1484,1510]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Protula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27CAFFA141D4A1597" box="[683,771,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Protula</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF854B1FC965FFD27D17FA141A2A1594" author="Kupriyanova, E. K. &amp; Jirkov, I. A." box="[787,1123,1484,1510]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="203 - 236" refId="ref63073" refString="Kupriyanova, E. K. &amp; Jirkov, I. A. (1997) Serpulidae (Annelida, Polychaeta) of the Arctic Ocean. Sarsia, 82, 203 - 236." type="journal article" year="1997">Kupriyanova &amp; Jirkov 1997</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The genera are separated mainly by the presence (
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC965FFD27FC3FA2B1C75167E" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1844" box="[455,572,1523,1548]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Apomatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27FC3FA2B1C75167E" box="[455,572,1523,1548]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Apomatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or absence (
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC965FFD27CE2FA2B1D77167E" baseAuthorityName="Kupriyanova &amp; Jirkov" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[742,830,1523,1548]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Protula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27CE2FA2B1D77167E" box="[742,830,1523,1548]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Protula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) of a soft vesicular operculum on an unmodified radiole. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF854B1FC965FFD27EF3F9C11F8F1641" author="Hanson, J." box="[247,454,1561,1587]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="581 - 584" refId="ref59817" refString="Hanson, J. (1948 a) The genera Apomatus and Protula (Polychaeta, Serpulidae). Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 27, 581 - 584." type="journal article" year="1948">Hanson’s (1948a)</bibRefCitation>
study on the pattern of blood vessels showed that 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC965FFD27A11F9C11AD61640" baseAuthorityName="Montagu" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[1045,1183,1561,1586]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Protula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tubularia">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27A11F9C11AD61640" box="[1045,1183,1561,1586]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">P. tubularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC965FFD27AAAF9C11B2A1640" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1844" box="[1198,1379,1561,1586]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Apomatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ampulliferus">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27AAAF9C11B2A1640" box="[1198,1379,1561,1586]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. ampulliferus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC965FFD27E93F9981F4F162B" authorityName="Marion &amp; Bobretzky" authorityYear="1875" box="[151,262,1600,1625]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Apomatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27E93F9981F4F162B" box="[151,262,1600,1625]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to each other, but dissimilar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC965FFD27D0CF9981DE9162B" baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[776,928,1600,1625]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Protula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="intestinum">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27D0CF9981DE9162B" box="[776,928,1600,1625]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">P. intestinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. She proposed that these genera should be fused. However, ten 
<bibRefCitation id="EF854B1FC965FFD27F9BF9BE1CF716F2" author="Hove, H. A. ten &amp; Pantus, F. J. A." box="[415,702,1638,1664]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="419 - 437" refId="ref61262" refString="Hove, H. A. ten &amp; Pantus, F. J. A. (1985) Distinguishing the genera Apomatus Philippi, 1844 and Protula Risso, 1826 (Polychaeta: Serpulidae). A further plea for a methodical approach to serpulid taxonomy. Zoologische Mededelingen (Leiden), 59, 419 - 437." type="journal article" year="1985">Hove &amp; Pantus (1985)</bibRefCitation>
studied over a 100 fresh specimens and found consistent differences in blood-vessel patterns between operculate and non-operculate specimens. They suggested that 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC965FFD27E93F96C1EA616BF" baseAuthorityName="Kupriyanova &amp; Jirkov" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[151,239,1716,1741]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Protula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27E93F96C1EA616BF" box="[151,239,1716,1741]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Protula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC965FFD27F33F96C1FE516BF" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1844" box="[311,428,1716,1741]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Apomatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27F33F96C1FE516BF" box="[311,428,1716,1741]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Apomatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are valid genera and that 
<bibRefCitation id="EF854B1FC965FFD27D02F96C1D8016BC" author="Hanson, J." box="[774,969,1716,1742]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="581 - 584" refId="ref59817" refString="Hanson, J. (1948 a) The genera Apomatus and Protula (Polychaeta, Serpulidae). Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 27, 581 - 584." type="journal article" year="1948">Hanson (1948a)</bibRefCitation>
mistook an 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC965FFD27A6BF96C1AAD16BF" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1844" box="[1135,1252,1716,1741]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Apomatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27A6BF96C1AAD16BF" box="[1135,1252,1716,1741]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Apomatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimen that incidentally lost its operculum for 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC965FFD27C2DF9031CFB1686" baseAuthorityName="Montagu" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[553,690,1755,1780]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Protula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tubularia">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC965FFD27C2DF9031CFB1686" box="[553,690,1755,1780]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">P. tubularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This controversy is yet to be resolved, probably with the aid of molecular genetics.
</paragraph>
